	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jul 31st 10:01 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.19]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am a 34 dwarf cleric and need some help as to where to be able to get groups<br><br>I have spent the last about 12 levels grouping in HighKeep... and am now moving on for other places... I got my L34 spells and am now looking for a place where i can get cash and xp (but more important to get groups easily as i do not have patience to sit for hours waiting for a group)... <br><br>I headed to RM having been there with a guild group while playing my druid) and have been unable to get a group for the last 2 days... will probably try to head for MM now, but wondering if anyone had any other suggestions for zones that would be relatively easy to get to for me.&nbsp;&nbsp;My dwarf is (most likely) not too well liked at the OT outpost, therefore that would be a difficult zone to get to.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102824343558211></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102824343558211><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=102824343558211>RE: Need help for a place to get groups</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=102824343558211#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=153318><span id=Scholar>Nrewfin</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>15 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 1st 7:10 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I as a dwarf cleric as well, leveled to 35 in highkeep, and then moved to Great Divide.<br><br>Great Divide has a few options of stuff to kill, all of varying levels.<br><br> - Tizmacks will be the easiest things to kill in a group.&nbsp;&nbsp;People in their upper 20's to lower 30's group here.  They do not drop any &quot;cash&quot;, but do drop velium weapons which sell for 3-5pp each, and also tizmack armor which can be sold to a merchant, or auctioned if you find a buyer.<br><br> - Cave Kodiaks are the next place you would probably group.  Levels here for you would probably be low 30's, (so now since you are 34), up to 39, 40 or so.  These bears, with the exception of the named spawn, Icetooth, do not drop any cash.  Icetooth himself drops about 6pp and usually Icetooth's claws which are worth about 70pp.  The rest of the bears uncommonly drop kodiak claws, kodiak pelts, hardened kodiak leather bracers.  These are again worth about 3-5pp to merchants.<br><br> - Frost Giants.  These mean guys hang out near the East Wastes zone, and have a fort near there as well.  These kills are probably best for mid to upper 30's to lower 40's to be safe but the scouts and berserkers can be handeled by a good group of mid 30's.  These guys DO drop cash, as well as velium weapons, same as the tizmacks had.  They also drop Frost Giant Toes and Heads which are used for the 1st and 2nd prayer shawl quest, which is a progressive tradeskill quest, 8 quests in all, the 8th shawl is a very nice prize to adorn on your shoulders.<br><br> - Finally Shardwurms.  Shardwurms also drop cash, and you can get groups killing these from mid to upper 30's to lower 40's as well.  The Glowing Wurms here drop the Glowing Shardwurm Bile which would be needed for your 5th shawl quest if you would be lucky enough to loot them.  <br>Shardwurms deep inside the cave, (I believe they are Guardian Shardwurms) have the chance to drop velious spells, including your 44 spell, Celestial Healing. <br><br>As far as grouping in Rathe Mountains..  I tried to do the same.  The time spent Looking For Group there to get cash could be better spent in some other zone fighting regular mobs that have some kind of loot.  You'd be getting experience and cash at the same time instead of sitting around, LFG.  When you get Retribution, (can't remember if your next DD is Retribution or Reckoning), you can solo these guys here but with a lot of downtime.  Again I feel fighting in another zone is more worth while.  Duoing with a 50+ mage friend of mine here worked well, we were able to handle 4 giants on us at one time.  If you ahve any pet class friends, consider asking them to go there with ya )<br><br>At 40, after bears, I left GD and didn't do much with Giants or Wurms.  You could then go to either Solusek B (Nagafen's Lair), Zone in is in Lavastorm.  Cash here is pretty good and you could go all the way up to 50 or so if you wanted to.    Your other option is the Dreadlands.  Cash here too on almost every mob, and some bronze armor and fine steel weapons.  Both zones can take you to level 50.  <br><br>Good luck, Brother Dwarf Cleric!<br><br>Nrewfin Givinglife<br>55th Templar of Brell<br>The Seventh Hammer<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
